QUALIFICATION: Hendel (1908) was the first after Meigen (1800) to give characters to differentiate the taxon (reproducing Meigen?s characters) and to treat Polyxena as valid, which makes the name available from that work with Meigen as author. Hendel (1908) did not include any species. Stone (1941) was the first to include a species, Cordyla fusca Meigen, 1804, which is the type species by subsequent designation. Cordyla fusca Meigen, 1804 is currently treated in Cordyla Meigen, 1803, which makes Polyxena Meigen in Hendel, 1908 a junior synonym of Cordyla Meigen, 1803

AUTHOR: Bezzi

PUB_PUB_PARENT_JOURNAL_TITLE: Wiener Entomologische Zeitung
PUB_PUB_FORMATTED: Bezzi, M. 1907. Nomenklatorisches über Dipteren. Wiener Entomologische Zeitung 26: 51-56

QUALIFICATION: Hendel (1908: 48) was the first after Meigen (1800) to give characters to differentiate the taxon (reproducing Meigen?s characters) and to treat Fungivora as valid, which makes the name available from that work with Meigen as author. Hendel (1908) included two nominal species. Coquillett (1910: 545) designated the second of these two, Tipula agarici Villers, 1789, which is the type species by subsequent designation. Tipula agarici Villers, 1789 is currently treated in Mycetophila Meigen, 1803, which makes Fungivora Meigen in Hendel, 1908 a junior synonym of Mycetophila Meigen, 1803 (see Evenhuis & Pope 2017)
